For more convenient sensing of Cr(VI) via naked eyes, paper-based sensors were constructed using filter paper impregnated with the solution of N,S-BCDs. The sensors exhibits a magnificent fluorescence quenching effect at a concentration of 0.98 mM (Fig. 6

                        ), which presents that they are used for the exploration of Cr(VI) in the waste water. Table 2
                         summarizes the efficiencies of BCDs by various natural carbon sources on sensing Cr(VI).
